@startuml
title Entity Management in TwelveLabs
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  ArrowFontColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #05D887
  ParticipantFontColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantFontStyle bold
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #05D887
  ActorFontColor #111111
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F4FFF9
  BorderColor #05D887
  FontColor #111111
}
actor User
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "Flask API" as API
participant "OpenCV / InsightFace\nFace Detection" as FaceCV
participant "TwelveLabs\nAssets API" as Assets
participant "TwelveLabs\nEntity API" as EntityAPI
database "Entity Collection" as EntityStore
User -> FE: Click "Add Entity"
FE -> API: GET /api/entities
API -> EntityAPI: List entities in collection
EntityAPI --> API: existing entities
API --> FE: entities list
FE --> User: Show AddEntityModal
User -> FE: Upload reference photo
FE -> API: POST /api/detect-faces\nimage file
API -> FaceCV: Detect faces and prepare preview crops
note right of FaceCV
ModeL
OpenCV ResNet10 SSD detects face boxes.
end note
FaceCV --> API: face boxes and preview crops
API --> FE: detected faces
FE --> User: Show detected faces for selection
User -> FE: Select face crop and enter name
User -> FE: Click "Register"
FE -> API: POST /api/entities/upload-face\nimage, name, description, preview
API -> Assets: Upload selected face image
Assets --> API: asset id
API -> EntityAPI: Ensure entity collection exists
EntityAPI --> API: collection id
API -> EntityAPI: Create entity with uploaded face asset
note right of EntityAPI
Model
TwelveLabs stores the reference face as an entity.
That entity can later be used in entity search
on the indexed videos.
end note
EntityAPI -> EntityStore: Store entity, asset link, and metadata
EntityStore --> EntityAPI: entity available
EntityAPI --> API: entity id, name, status
API --> FE: created entity
FE --> User: Entity appears in entity list
@enduml